  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Girls Education Challenge (GEC-T) STAR G Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention will promote an inclusive approach and mainstream disability in all project activities of the ongoing Successful Transition and Advancement of Rights for Girls (STAR-G) project in Mozambique led by Save the Children International and the implementing partners HOPEM, CESC, and PROGRESSO.  The project aims to strengthen the capacities of partners (implementing partners, teachers, local authorities and community representatives) to improve access as well as transition &amp; learning outcomes to an inclusive &amp; quality education and other services for STARG cohorts of girls with disabilities in order to promote their rights to education.</narrative>
  </description>
